  "doc_id": "18926",
  "text": "Here we present data from a procedure with automated spot picking, digestion, peak detection, and database search. For further evaluation we applied a new version of MSScreener comprising elimination of contaminants, detection of neighbor spot contamination, cluster analysis, and identification of minor components of a spot. The antigenic proteins detected in spots identified in former investigations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] were analyzed in detail to assure that the antigenicity is caused by the formerly identified protein and not by a minor component. As special cases a dimerization of alkyl hydroperoxide reductase (HP1563), the degradation pattern of GroEL, and the fragmentation of ␥-glutamyltranspeptidase were elucidated.",
